%N A155073 Expansion of (1 + 6*x)/(1 - 12*x - 8*x^2).
%C A155073 Number of matchings in the hexagonal snake graph on 5*n + 1 vertices with cut vertices at distance 3. - _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 18 2026
%H A155073 Tomislav Došlić and Frode Måløy, <a href="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.disc.2009.11.026">Chain hexagonal cacti: Matchings and independent sets</a>, Discr. Math., 310 (2010), 1676-1690.
%H A155073 Eric Weisstein's World of Mathematics, <a href="https://mathworld.wolfram.com/IndependentEdgeSet.html">Independent Edge Set</a>.
%H A155073 <a href="/index/Rec#order_02">Index entries for linear recurrences with constant coefficients</a>, signature (12,8).
%e A155073 From _Andrew Howroyd_, Jul 18 2026: (Start)
%e A155073 Illustration of the hexagonal snake graph for n = 3:
%e A155073         o---o   o---o   o---o
%e A155073        /     \ /     \ /     \
%e A155073       o       o       o       o
%e A155073        \     / \     / \     /
%e A155073         o---o   o---o   o---o
%e A155073 (End)
%t A155073 CoefficientList[Series[(1+6x)/(1-12x-8x^2),{x,0,20}],x] (* or *) LinearRecurrence[ {12,8},{1,18},20]
%Y A155073 Relating to hexagonal snake graph: A153709, A155049, A157765 (independent sets), A275903 (maximal matchings).
